records.addlTxt:
Defendant Jacob W Lange in court, in custody, with attorney John Joseph Grau.   Pablo Galaviz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Patricia Deklotz spoke on behalf of victim, Kettle Moraine School District. Defense presents arguments.   Defendant's parents address the Court.  

The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

Count #2:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

12 MONTHS JAIL;

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEARS;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Maintain Absolute Sobriety; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*Any other term deemed appropriate by agent. 
*Mental Health Evaluation and follow through. 
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*Perform 40 Hours of Community Service for each year of probation.
*Obtain GED or HSED.
RESTITUTION: TO BE DETERMINED;

COURT COSTS:  $278.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

Expunction is conditionally granted upon verification of completion of sentence, payment of all costs/fees and no new law violations.

Count #3:

JAIL:  9 MONTHS, First 4 months Straight time, Followed by 5 Months with Huber release.  Release for work and treatment. (apply 18 days credit to Straight time portion of sentence); (commencing forthwith)

COURT COSTS: $243.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation on count #2)

DNA SURCHARGE: $200.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

Request for expunction is denied by the Court on Count #3.
